-- в”Ђв”Ђ Juro в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$AI-native, browser-based contract lifecycle management platform for creating, negotiating and managing contracts.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Enterprise$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Custom pricing (typically $15K-$60K/year)$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2016, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE($q$51-200 employees$q$, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE($q$London, United Kingdom$q$, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Juro Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Juro review 2026: AI-native contract management platform. Explore browser-based editing, workflow automation, pricing tiers, pros, cons and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Juro is a British legal technology company that builds an AI-native, browser-based contract lifecycle management (CLM) platform, founded in 2016 by Richard Mabey and Pavel Kovalevich. The company is headquartered in London, with an engineering hub in Riga, Latvia, and opened a United States headquarters in Boston, Massachusetts, in 2025 to better serve its growing North American customer base. Juro's core technical differentiator is that contracts are created, negotiated, signed, and managed entirely inside a browser-native editor rather than as Microsoft Word documents routed through email and separate e-signature tools; this browser-first architecture allows Juro to layer structured data extraction, AI-assisted drafting and review, real-time collaborative redlining, conditional approval workflows, and native e-signature directly onto the contract itself, and to expose contract terms as queryable structured data rather than locked inside static PDFs. The platform's feature set spans the full contract lifecycle: templated contract creation with dynamic clauses and conditional logic, AI-powered contract generation and clause suggestions, real-time in-browser collaboration and version control, configurable multi-step approval workflows, built-in e-signature, a searchable contract repository with AI-driven data extraction (dates, values, parties, obligations) for reporting and renewal tracking, and integrations with tools like Slack, HubSpot, Salesforce, and Workday so that non-legal teams (sales, HR, procurement) can self-serve routine contracts within guardrails set by legal. Under CEO Richard Mabey, Juro has raised roughly $36 million in disclosed venture funding from investors including Eight Roads, Union Square Ventures (USV), Point Nine Capital, and Seedcamp, along with angel backing from founders of Indeed, Gumtree, and Wise; its most notable round was a $23 million Series B led by Eight Roads Ventures in January 2022, positioned to fund international expansion and deeper AI capabilities. Pricing is not self-serve or publicly itemized per seat; Juro sells annual contracts typically ranging from roughly $15,000 to $60,000 per year depending on company size and feature tier, with its Scale and Enterprise plans offering unlimited user seats rather than per-user pricing, a deliberate positioning against legacy CLM and e-signature competitors that charge $30-80 per user per month, which can make Juro more cost-predictable for legal teams that need to give many non-legal employees contract access. Juro targets in-house legal, revenue operations, HR, and procurement teams at mid-market and enterprise companies, particularly fast-scaling SaaS and technology companies, who need to reduce contract turnaround time and give business teams safe self-serve access to contracting. Its named competitors include Ironclad, DocuSign CLM (and DocuSign's e-signature product more broadly), ContractPodAi, LinkSquares, PandaDoc, and Concord; Juro differentiates through its fully browser-native (non-Word, non-PDF) editing experience, its unlimited-seat flat-fee pricing model, and its emphasis on turning contracts into structured, queryable data rather than static signed documents.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'b3138f4f-7b47-4597-bf67-8ea806a1edd0';

